      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SKETCH (2) did enough first up here over 1200m, battling on well for third, beaten 2.5 lengths. That trip was always going to be on the sharp side, expect quick improvement going to 1400m now from a soft draw. Her form last time in reads well for this. WHITE HOT MAMA (3) won well first up here having shown ability in three runs last time in. She looks to have come back much better and can go on with it from a good draw. ROSE SANGRIA (1) just got over the top of them last start at Mornington over 1200m and looks suited up in trip off that win. She can measure up. TILL QUEEN (4) struggled in town last time, the maiden win prior was solid and she could bounce back. FEARLESS MONARCH (5) can be forgiven for the heavy track flop last time.",
